Applies to:
  - `src/en/data/averaged_perceptron_tagger_eng.json.gz`, generated by
    `tools/export_nltk_tagger.py` from the `nltk_data` resource
    `averaged_perceptron_tagger_eng` (downloaded via `nltk.download(...)`),
    re-serialized into a plain JSON asset so the TypeScript port can
    re-implement the same tagging logic without depending on NLTK at
    runtime.
  - `tests/fixtures/stemmer_fixture.json.gz` and
    `tests/fixtures/pos_fixture.json.gz` also depend, at generation time
    only, on NLTK's `EnglishStemmer` (Snowball/Porter2, BSD-licensed within
    NLTK) and this tagger resource respectively, to produce reference
    output the TypeScript implementation is checked against. NLTK itself is
    never a runtime dependency of the published TypeScript package -- see
    `tools/README.md`.
